<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Hurl" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Hurl,</orth> 1) tr. to throw violently and impetuously: <bibl n="shak. lc 87" default="NO" valid="yes">Compl. 87</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 2.2.137" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. II, 2, 137</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.2.87" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 2, 87</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 1.1.146" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 1, 146</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.4.46" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 4, 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.220" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 3, 220</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.4.205" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 4, 205</bibl>. 206 (Qq <emph>throw</emph>). <bibl n="shak. r3 3.7.35" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 7, 35</bibl> (<emph>--ed up their caps</emph>). <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.86" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 86</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 5.1.64" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. V, 1, 64</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 5.2.274" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. V, 2, 274</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 1.2.127" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. I, 2, 127</bibl>.<lb />2) intr. to move in a wild and confused manner: <cit><quote>these are but wild and --ing words,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 1.5.133" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 5, 133</bibl></cit> (Qq <emph>whirling</emph>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>